CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1958, pg. A11 reads: "Dr. Gragg Speaks - Dr. Rose S. Gragg (standing in center) is surrounded by other program participants at the afternoon Women's Day program at Bethlehem Baptist Church, McKeesport, last Sunday. Seated, left to right, are: Mmes. Gladys McNairy, Ellis Blockson, George W.  White, Mary Alexander, Pauline Young, Paul Dippolito, J. Harold Hayes, Walter Lundberg and Sadie Carter.  Standing far right is Mrs. Georgia Pettiford, one of the ushers, and Mrs. Hazel Garland, mistress of ceremonies...- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated, from left: Gladys McNairy, Ellis Blockson, Mrs. George W.  White, Mary Alexander, Pauline Young, Mrs. Paul Dippolito, Mrs. J. Harold Hayes, Mrs. Walter Lundberg, and Sadie Carter; standing in center, Dr. Rose S. Gregg, guest speaker; in background is Georgia Pettiford and Hazel Garland, gathered at banquet table in Bethlehem Baptist Church for Women's Day program, McKeesport
